@gator159 The only system Nintendo has made which was a "generation behind" was the Wii. In all other cases, they have been a serious competitor.
The N64 was more powerful than the PSX and Sega Saturn, and the GameCube was more powerful than the PS2 and Dreamcast (the Xbox came out much later and was more powerful than all of them, probably because it came out much later).
It remains to be seen whether the Wii U will be a "generation behind."
